result.execSummary:
The defendant Dale T. Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.
Concurrent with: Any existing period of supervision.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Defendant to maintain timely, uninterrupted payments of $65.00 per month as to the arrearages existing in Waushara Co Case No. 1985FA000135.   Payments are to be made monthly and payable on the 5th of each month until further order of the Court.  The Supervising Agent shall file an Affidavit with the Court bi-monthly that shall verify that the payment schedule is being maintained.  If the Affidavit is not received, a probation review hearing will be scheduled.   All payments are to be paid through the Wisconsin Support Collections Trust Fund (WISCTF), not through the Department of Corrections.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 2:41 PM: Defendant Dale T. Anderson in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich.  Steven Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per ADA:  Terms of resolution recited.  Terms to be entirely argued.  State will cap and argue for 4 yrs probation with 6 mos cond'l time and conditions.  Def and Counsel concur w/State's recital.  Court entertains waiver of pre-lim hearing in its entirety.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of pre-lim hearing.  Def BOT.  INFO Filed - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Per Atty Ulrich - based upon new information brought to light, believes it would be beneficial for the Court to order a PSI.  State would not oppose PSI if in fact being requested.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Treatment/Meds not serving any impairment on proceeding today.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct Nos 1 and 2:  NC  Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.  Ct Nos 3 thru 8 all DRI.   Per Atty Ulrich - Def already on supervision in his home county and due to discharge in March.  Approx Arrears of $84000 with almost $63000 of that amount being interest.  Based upon discussions, Court will ask that matter proceed to sentencing today.  Victim Rights in compliance.  Defendant is prepared to proceed today to SEH.  Argument by ADA.  Argument by Atty Ulrich - argues against imposition of cond'l jail and questions if means exist to maintain any payments. Requests probation with terms as per Agent.  Statement by Def:  Yes.  The Court:  Both Counts S/W -  4 yrs probation. Concurrent to any existing period of supervision.  Conditions:  As to Ct 1 only:  6 mos WCJ I/S - provided that on the 5th of every single month, make a payment of $65 toward the arrearage owing - $65/mo payment only - paid every month on the 5th of each month - bi-monthly an Agent to file an Affidavit with this court that timely payment of the $65 has been maintained so the Court is aware from the Agent that payments are being made - Agent to verify with the Court that payments have been made.  No employment condition - not employable.  If agent does not supply affidavit a PRH will be scheduled.  Court Costs - 60 DTP or PP.  Appeal Rights Given.
